1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,670
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,753 --> 00:00:08,216
["Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,299 --> 00:00:09,300
♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪

4
00:00:09,384 --> 00:00:10,635
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

5
00:00:10,719 --> 00:00:12,804
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

6
00:00:12,887 --> 00:00:16,558
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i>
<i>In the tangle…</i> ♪

7
00:00:16,641 --> 00:00:18,560
[Dmitri] <i>Do you know where she's going?</i>

8
00:00:18,643 --> 00:00:20,186
[Red] <i>Maybe to have</i>
<i>clothes made by a tailor.</i>

9
00:00:20,270 --> 00:00:22,772
[Dmitri] <i>No way.</i>
<i>That Master Cutter is not a tailor.</i>

10
00:00:23,356 --> 00:00:26,067
[receptionist] Miss, Miss!
Your shades! Miss!

11
00:00:26,151 --> 00:00:27,527
[Atoy] <i>Do you want me to give it to her?</i>

12
00:00:27,610 --> 00:00:29,195
[Dmitri, in English]
<i>Tell your tracker to back off.</i>

13
00:00:29,279 --> 00:00:31,364
[Mercado, in English] <i>Abort engagement</i>
<i>with Audrey Regalia.</i>

14
00:00:31,448 --> 00:00:35,160
Mr. Regalia requested
not to meet with his daughter.

15
00:00:35,243 --> 00:00:37,162
[Atoy, in English] <i>All right.</i>
<i>Uh, copy that, sir.</i>

16
00:00:37,245 --> 00:00:39,873
I haven't established contact
with the subject yet.

17
00:00:39,956 --> 00:00:43,042
[in English] And now Audrey
wants to hire him to look for this guy.

18
00:00:43,126 --> 00:00:45,003
[Dmitri] <i>The one she met on the island.</i>

19
00:00:45,086 --> 00:00:46,588
<i>He'll definitely find him.</i>

20
00:00:46,671 --> 00:00:47,922
[in English] Ah, excuse me!

21
00:00:48,006 --> 00:00:49,424
[in English] Those are my shades.

22
00:00:50,592 --> 00:00:52,343
[upbeat music continues]

23
00:00:52,427 --> 00:00:54,763
PREVIOUSLY

24
00:00:54,846 --> 00:00:56,097
Audrey Regalia?

25
00:00:56,681 --> 00:00:59,309
- That's so different. Audrey, Elaine…
- Wait a minute.

26
00:00:59,392 --> 00:01:00,727
What about you?

27
00:01:00,810 --> 00:01:04,189
I don't know your real name up to now.

28
00:01:04,272 --> 00:01:07,150
[Tonet] <i>I just wanted</i>
<i>to thank you personally.</i>

29
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:10,653
<i>Thank you for saving</i>
<i>my brother's life and mine.</i>

30
00:01:10,737 --> 00:01:12,697
[music continues]

31
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,284
[sobs]

32
00:01:16,367 --> 00:01:18,119
[Audrey] <i>So, that's why you</i>
<i>stopped me from talking</i>

33
00:01:18,203 --> 00:01:19,329
<i>to the tracker behind my back.</i>

34
00:01:19,412 --> 00:01:21,247
[Audrey] He means nothing in my life.

35
00:01:21,331 --> 00:01:23,750
[in English] We mean nothing
to each other.

36
00:01:24,459 --> 00:01:27,420
[Dmitri, in English] <i>Finally,</i>
<i>you've come to your senses.</i>

37
00:01:32,467 --> 00:01:33,968
[Ibyang] Okay! Higher!

38
00:01:34,052 --> 00:01:35,386
Higher… Up.

39
00:01:35,470 --> 00:01:37,388
Ah, ah… Close. Ah, not yet.

40
00:01:37,472 --> 00:01:38,932
- Wait, it's uneven.
- [Karla] Is it okay now?

41
00:01:39,015 --> 00:01:40,016
It's lopsided. Wait.

42
00:01:40,099 --> 00:01:42,644
- [Karla] I think it's level now!
- [Ibyang] Raise it a bit more. Higher!

43
00:01:42,727 --> 00:01:43,978
[Karla] This is fine.

44
00:01:48,274 --> 00:01:49,651
- Ibyang.
- [Ibyang] Mmm?

45
00:01:49,734 --> 00:01:51,194
What does that say?

46
00:01:51,277 --> 00:01:54,572
Well, it says, "Welcome back, Sis Tonet!"

47
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:56,658
Not that. There!

48
00:01:58,368 --> 00:02:01,204
[gentle music playing]

49
00:02:03,289 --> 00:02:04,332
[groans]

50
00:02:04,415 --> 00:02:05,500
Ouch!

51
00:02:06,417 --> 00:02:07,585
Something got in my eye!

52
00:02:07,669 --> 00:02:09,170
I can't read.

53
00:02:09,254 --> 00:02:11,673
Hey, I cleaned, you know.

54
00:02:12,632 --> 00:02:14,175
Really, Ibyang?

55
00:02:14,676 --> 00:02:16,136
You're making excuses.

56
00:02:16,636 --> 00:02:19,931
Why didn't you tell me you couldn't read?

57
00:02:20,014 --> 00:02:21,349
For real?

58
00:02:22,767 --> 00:02:24,894
You admitted it to Atoy first.

59
00:02:24,978 --> 00:02:27,355
I only found out from him?

60
00:02:27,438 --> 00:02:28,898
Aren't we close?

61
00:02:29,774 --> 00:02:33,736
Uh… I was embarrassed.

62
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:36,781
Come here.

63
00:02:37,323 --> 00:02:39,075
[gentle music continues]

64
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:43,037
There's nothing wrong
with admitting your weaknesses.

65
00:02:43,872 --> 00:02:47,500
You're young. You can still learn.

66
00:02:47,584 --> 00:02:50,753
Look at me. There's
no hope for me anymore.

67
00:02:50,837 --> 00:02:54,716
Correct. Ame, what's your flaw?

68
00:02:55,341 --> 00:02:57,218
Share it with us. No judgment.

69
00:02:57,302 --> 00:02:58,928
Well, my height.

70
00:02:59,012 --> 00:03:00,138
This is it, to the max.

71
00:03:00,221 --> 00:03:01,180
Oh, yes, right.

72
00:03:01,264 --> 00:03:02,390
[chuckles]

73
00:03:02,473 --> 00:03:07,812
Sis Karla, I'll guess your inadequacy.

74
00:03:07,896 --> 00:03:08,771
What?

75
00:03:08,855 --> 00:03:10,106
Suitors!

76
00:03:10,189 --> 00:03:11,482
You cheeky kid!

77
00:03:11,566 --> 00:03:12,483
[Ibyang chuckles]

78
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:14,402
Just you wait!
Who knows, I'll have one soon.

79
00:03:14,485 --> 00:03:16,112
Oh! She said soon!

80
00:03:16,195 --> 00:03:17,488
[chuckles] And got lost.

81
00:03:17,572 --> 00:03:19,741
- [Ame and Ibyang laugh]
- Are you ready? They're here!

82
00:03:19,824 --> 00:03:21,576
- Come on, come on.
- Let's go, let's go.

83
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:25,330
Ouch. [grunts softly]

84
00:03:26,331 --> 00:03:27,457
Aww.

85
00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:30,043
[in English] Welcome back!

86
00:03:30,126 --> 00:03:31,628
[pensive music playing]

87
00:03:31,711 --> 00:03:33,338
[Emerson clears throat] Ah, no. I just…

88
00:03:33,421 --> 00:03:34,756
I just accompanied her.

89
00:03:34,839 --> 00:03:37,675
I'm not literally returning because…

90
00:03:37,759 --> 00:03:39,052
it might make…

91
00:03:39,135 --> 00:03:42,013
Atoy insecure.

92
00:03:43,097 --> 00:03:45,558
Bro, we get it. No one asked.

93
00:03:45,642 --> 00:03:47,060
But we get it, we get it.

94
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:48,561
[chuckles]

95
00:03:48,645 --> 00:03:50,104
I'm just joking. We're good now.

96
00:03:50,188 --> 00:03:51,314
[chuckles]

97
00:03:51,397 --> 00:03:53,399
I missed you, Sis Tonet!

98
00:03:53,483 --> 00:03:54,525
Aww.

99
00:03:54,609 --> 00:03:56,402
Me too, baby girl!

100
00:03:56,486 --> 00:03:58,655
[light music playing]

101
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:01,157
I'm happy you're back.

102
00:04:01,741 --> 00:04:03,201
Oh?

103
00:04:03,284 --> 00:04:04,494
Really?

104
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:07,580
Yes. It's hard
not to have competition here.

105
00:04:08,081 --> 00:04:10,166
Oh, let's eat! Come on!

106
00:04:10,792 --> 00:04:12,710
- Let's eat, let's eat.
- [chattering]

107
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:13,711
You should eat.

108
00:04:13,795 --> 00:04:14,796
- Go, eat.
- [chattering]

109
00:04:14,879 --> 00:04:17,465
- Brother, you should eat here.
- Okay, okay.

110
00:04:17,548 --> 00:04:18,591
[in English] Let's eat.

111
00:04:18,675 --> 00:04:20,260
[Ame] You should eat a lot.

112
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:21,719
[light music continues]

113
00:04:21,803 --> 00:04:23,554
Give some to Emerson.

114
00:04:23,638 --> 00:04:25,056
Our savior.

115
00:04:25,139 --> 00:04:27,016
[lively chattering]

116
00:04:27,558 --> 00:04:30,144
[suave theme music playing]

117
00:04:38,861 --> 00:04:42,115
[sewing machine whirring]

118
00:04:42,198 --> 00:04:43,533
- [gun cocks]
- [gunshots]

119
00:04:43,616 --> 00:04:45,493
[gunshots blasting]

120
00:04:45,576 --> 00:04:47,787
[clicking]

121
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:50,331
[snipping]

122
00:04:50,415 --> 00:04:52,625
[electronic blipping]

123
00:04:55,795 --> 00:04:58,131
[music concludes]

124
00:05:01,050 --> 00:05:03,177
‪[sentimental music playing]

125
00:05:15,023 --> 00:05:16,441
[Audrey] <i>What do you think of me, huh?</i>

126
00:05:17,275 --> 00:05:18,943
That I haven't moved on from you?

127
00:05:19,736 --> 00:05:21,237
That I have no life?

128
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:24,240
[scoffs] For your information,

129
00:05:25,116 --> 00:05:29,620
eight years have passed,
and you never crossed my mind.

130
00:05:31,122 --> 00:05:33,833
[music concludes]

131
00:05:34,375 --> 00:05:38,129
[crickets chirping]

132
00:05:39,047 --> 00:05:40,715
Why are you here?

133
00:05:40,798 --> 00:05:42,467
The food is inside.

134
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:44,635
Uh…

135
00:05:44,719 --> 00:05:45,720
[clears throat]

136
00:05:45,803 --> 00:05:47,430
It's fine, Miss Cita.

137
00:05:47,513 --> 00:05:49,390
I'm not hungry yet.

138
00:05:50,767 --> 00:05:53,144
[gentle music playing]

139
00:05:53,227 --> 00:05:55,104
Even if you don't say it,

140
00:05:55,188 --> 00:05:57,315
I know something's bothering you.

141
00:05:57,940 --> 00:05:59,734
I have plenty of time.

142
00:06:00,818 --> 00:06:02,820
Before I came home here,

143
00:06:03,613 --> 00:06:06,115
I met a woman on the island.

144
00:06:06,783 --> 00:06:07,742
[music continues]

145
00:06:07,825 --> 00:06:10,453
But she vanished like a bubble.

146
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:13,873
Then after eight years,

147
00:06:14,832 --> 00:06:15,792
we saw each other again.

148
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:17,460
- Oh?
- At the hospital.

149
00:06:18,002 --> 00:06:19,295
And then? What happened?

150
00:06:19,378 --> 00:06:20,421
Did you get back together?

151
00:06:20,922 --> 00:06:22,006
No.

152
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:23,800
That won't happen.

153
00:06:27,261 --> 00:06:30,890
I thought we were okay, because…

154
00:06:31,557 --> 00:06:33,684
we had a connection, a spark.

155
00:06:34,602 --> 00:06:36,020
But I guess it wasn't real.

156
00:06:36,104 --> 00:06:38,147
It was only me who thought that.

157
00:06:41,692 --> 00:06:45,404
Looks like this woman
had an impact on you.

158
00:06:45,988 --> 00:06:49,575
This is the first time
I've seen you brokenhearted.

159
00:06:54,330 --> 00:06:55,331
No, not really.

160
00:06:55,414 --> 00:06:56,791
C'mon.

161
00:06:56,874 --> 00:06:58,292
[in English] "Brokenhearted."

162
00:06:59,377 --> 00:07:01,212
No, and…

163
00:07:03,506 --> 00:07:04,966
- Oh?
- That was long ago.

164
00:07:05,049 --> 00:07:06,134
[both chuckle]

165
00:07:06,217 --> 00:07:07,718
That was long ago, Miss Cita.
It's nothing.

166
00:07:07,802 --> 00:07:08,719
Hmm?

167
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:09,929
It's nothing.

168
00:07:11,681 --> 00:07:13,099
All right.

169
00:07:13,182 --> 00:07:14,600
If you say so.

170
00:07:16,269 --> 00:07:17,478
Um…

171
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:20,440
Three minutes, okay.

172
00:07:21,065 --> 00:07:22,608
The food's ready.

173
00:07:23,192 --> 00:07:25,278
Okay. I'll follow.

174
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:33,244
[deep exhale]

175
00:07:33,327 --> 00:07:39,292
[music brightens]

176
00:07:45,423 --> 00:07:46,257
‪[scoffs]

177
00:07:49,177 --> 00:07:50,636
[Gavin] Your flight is this weekend?

178
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,889
Why does it seem so sudden?

179
00:07:53,556 --> 00:07:55,308
Let's just say, I woke up,

180
00:07:55,391 --> 00:07:58,227
and thought I wanted
to go back to the States.

181
00:07:59,061 --> 00:08:01,898
So, hurry up, I still have
a lot to buy at the mall.

182
00:08:01,981 --> 00:08:03,274
[in English] Wait.

183
00:08:03,357 --> 00:08:05,526
What about your mystery island guy?

184
00:08:06,986 --> 00:08:08,821
[in English] He's no longer a mystery.

185
00:08:09,405 --> 00:08:11,908
[in English] He's a disappointment
and not worth it.

186
00:08:11,991 --> 00:08:13,367
[smirks]

187
00:08:13,451 --> 00:08:16,787
I have a feeling that's really the reason
why you suddenly want to leave.

188
00:08:18,247 --> 00:08:19,790
[Audrey groans]

189
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:22,585
[pensive music playing]

190
00:08:22,668 --> 00:08:23,794
[in English] Are you okay?

191
00:08:26,047 --> 00:08:27,632
It's just this pain in my side.

192
00:08:27,715 --> 00:08:29,300
[in English] It's been happening
a lot lately.

193
00:08:29,383 --> 00:08:30,301
Huh?

194
00:08:30,384 --> 00:08:31,302
Since when?

195
00:08:31,385 --> 00:08:33,471
Have you had a check-up, Auntie?

196
00:08:33,554 --> 00:08:34,722
[in English] I'll be fine.

197
00:08:34,805 --> 00:08:36,516
Let's just go home, please.

198
00:08:36,599 --> 00:08:37,642
No, no.

199
00:08:37,725 --> 00:08:38,976
I'll take you to the hospital.

200
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:40,561
[tense music playing]

201
00:08:40,645 --> 00:08:41,979
[groans]

202
00:08:44,273 --> 00:08:47,527
- [music intensifies]
- [pained breathing]

203
00:08:50,488 --> 00:08:51,822
[music fades]

204
00:08:51,906 --> 00:08:53,533
[sewing machine whirring]

205
00:08:53,616 --> 00:08:54,951
[sewing machine clicks, stops]

206
00:08:55,618 --> 00:08:59,205
[sewing machine whirring]

207
00:09:04,293 --> 00:09:07,046
[door chime clinks]

208
00:09:10,132 --> 00:09:11,175
[sewing machine clicks, stops]

209
00:09:11,259 --> 00:09:13,052
Whose rush order is that?

210
00:09:13,135 --> 00:09:16,305
I didn't know orders came in yesterday.

211
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:19,934
No new orders, Miss Cita.
I'm just finishing the old ones here.

212
00:09:22,019 --> 00:09:23,479
Ah.

213
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:24,939
If your father were alive,

214
00:09:25,022 --> 00:09:30,194
he wouldn't want
you wasting fabric and losing sleep.

215
00:09:31,779 --> 00:09:34,699
[rousing music playing]

216
00:09:35,741 --> 00:09:38,244
[sewing machine whirring]

217
00:09:39,912 --> 00:09:41,205
Looks like, uh…

218
00:09:41,289 --> 00:09:42,206
[sewing machine clicks, stops]

219
00:09:42,290 --> 00:09:44,000
…you're losing sleep over that.

220
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:48,879
Your coffee from last night is still here.

221
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:52,508
What's going on with you?

222
00:09:54,468 --> 00:09:55,803
Oh.

223
00:09:55,886 --> 00:09:57,805
I know you.

224
00:09:59,515 --> 00:10:02,435
When you have something
you can't say from your heart,

225
00:10:02,518 --> 00:10:04,520
you pour it into sewing.

226
00:10:05,229 --> 00:10:06,606
The last time you did that…

227
00:10:06,689 --> 00:10:07,607
[sewing machine clicks, stops]

228
00:10:07,690 --> 00:10:11,736
…was when you found out
your mother had cancer.

229
00:10:11,819 --> 00:10:14,739
[melancholic music playing]

230
00:10:14,822 --> 00:10:18,618
You know, when I'm gone…

231
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:24,332
things or people
that hurt you won't stop coming.

232
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,627
That's just how the world is.

233
00:10:28,210 --> 00:10:30,796
[sewing machine whirring]

234
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:32,632
I'm fine, Dad.

235
00:10:34,717 --> 00:10:36,260
I know you're not.

236
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:38,888
So don't say you're okay.

237
00:10:40,431 --> 00:10:41,891
You know…

238
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:44,935
not everyone can read you.

239
00:10:45,561 --> 00:10:48,022
If your heart is hurting,

240
00:10:49,065 --> 00:10:55,655
maybe it's better to have
someone to talk to, whatever it is.

241
00:10:56,697 --> 00:10:57,990
You know…

242
00:10:58,741 --> 00:11:01,619
your heart will feel lighter, and…

243
00:11:03,037 --> 00:11:05,039
you'll save fabric too.

244
00:11:05,122 --> 00:11:06,957
[sewing machine whirring]

245
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:12,380
[music brightens]

246
00:11:18,135 --> 00:11:19,929
Auntie, I got in touch
with Grandpa already.

247
00:11:20,012 --> 00:11:21,847
[in English] He's on his way here.

248
00:11:22,348 --> 00:11:23,933
[breathing heavily] Thank you.

249
00:11:24,016 --> 00:11:28,062
[suspicious music playing]

250
00:11:29,105 --> 00:11:33,734
Ms. Regalia, I already saw the result
of your abdominal scan in the lab.

251
00:11:33,818 --> 00:11:35,903
And based on that,
your appendix is inflamed,

252
00:11:35,986 --> 00:11:37,696
and it's close to rupturing.

253
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:40,032
I'll give you medicine to ease the pain,

254
00:11:40,116 --> 00:11:43,536
but it needs to be surgically removed
within a few hours.

255
00:11:43,619 --> 00:11:45,121
I'll schedule you for the OR.

256
00:11:45,204 --> 00:11:46,622
Wait, Doc.

257
00:11:47,373 --> 00:11:49,375
[in English] For an appendectomy, Doc?

258
00:11:50,626 --> 00:11:52,837
[in English] Th-That's impossible.

259
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,463
[in English] I already had one.

260
00:11:55,256 --> 00:11:56,966
My appendix was removed.

261
00:11:57,049 --> 00:11:58,968
Are you sure, ma'am?

262
00:11:59,593 --> 00:12:02,263
Where were you operated on? When was this?

263
00:12:02,346 --> 00:12:04,473
Ah, a long time ago, in the States.

264
00:12:05,307 --> 00:12:07,476
About eight years ago?

265
00:12:09,186 --> 00:12:11,313
The scar is still here.

266
00:12:13,441 --> 00:12:17,027
[in English] Um, ma'am,
that is a low transverse incision.

267
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:19,071
Or what we call the bikini cut

268
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:20,739
of a caesarean section.

269
00:12:20,823 --> 00:12:22,241
[music subsides]

270
00:12:22,324 --> 00:12:24,368
[in English] Caesarean section?

271
00:12:26,829 --> 00:12:27,830
‪[tense music playing]

272
00:12:27,913 --> 00:12:30,666
Are you saying I was pregnant before?

273
00:12:30,749 --> 00:12:32,168
[music intensifies]

274
00:12:33,544 --> 00:12:36,172
Auntie, you didn't know?

275
00:12:51,645 --> 00:12:52,771
Miss Cita.

276
00:12:54,023 --> 00:12:57,651
Is it normal to keep
thinking about someone,

277
00:12:58,194 --> 00:13:01,030
even if you know
your relationship was shallow?

278
00:13:02,198 --> 00:13:04,408
It's not shallow if it feels that way.

279
00:13:05,117 --> 00:13:09,413
Love isn't measured by time.

280
00:13:09,497 --> 00:13:11,248
[gentle music playing]

281
00:13:11,332 --> 00:13:12,541
Ah.

282
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:15,836
Well, it didn't last anyway, so…

283
00:13:16,712 --> 00:13:20,216
looks like I just need to move on.

284
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:27,681
[Cita] Why don't you take
a vacation abroad?

285
00:13:27,765 --> 00:13:30,434
You've earned a lot from your side job.

286
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:32,520
Treat yourself to a good time.

287
00:13:32,603 --> 00:13:36,232
Miss Cita, everything I spend on is here.

288
00:13:36,857 --> 00:13:40,861
Of course, I spend on updating
the equipment here.

289
00:13:41,654 --> 00:13:43,906
Buying new weapons

290
00:13:44,406 --> 00:13:46,659
and building the secret room, right?

291
00:13:47,785 --> 00:13:49,745
But you've saved a lot.

292
00:13:49,828 --> 00:13:51,497
Use it!

293
00:13:53,290 --> 00:13:56,752
Miss Cita, we stay low-key.

294
00:13:56,835 --> 00:13:58,504
I can afford to live comfortably.

295
00:13:58,587 --> 00:13:59,964
I can afford it.

296
00:14:00,464 --> 00:14:01,924
But no.

297
00:14:02,007 --> 00:14:05,636
I'm known as a simple tailor,

298
00:14:05,719 --> 00:14:07,221
and that's what we'll keep doing.

299
00:14:07,304 --> 00:14:09,765
I don't want people
knowing more about my life.

300
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:13,269
Okay, but…

301
00:14:13,352 --> 00:14:16,814
why not renovate this tailoring shop?

302
00:14:16,897 --> 00:14:19,191
Make it modern, like in the mall.

303
00:14:19,275 --> 00:14:20,276
[in English] Modern?

304
00:14:20,359 --> 00:14:21,443
This?

305
00:14:22,528 --> 00:14:23,737
Miss Cita, no.

306
00:14:23,821 --> 00:14:25,239
This is fine.

307
00:14:25,906 --> 00:14:28,617
I'm okay with the layout, and…

308
00:14:29,827 --> 00:14:32,288
of course, this reminds me of Dad.

309
00:14:32,371 --> 00:14:34,373
Look at his pictures. See?!

310
00:14:34,456 --> 00:14:40,838
This is the only memory
I have of my father.

311
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:49,471
Atoy, have you found the one
who hit and run your father?

312
00:14:50,639 --> 00:14:52,308
Well…

313
00:14:53,309 --> 00:14:56,645
Colonel Mercado helped me.

314
00:14:57,855 --> 00:15:00,900
We searched for months, but…

315
00:15:01,692 --> 00:15:03,193
we got nothing.

316
00:15:04,361 --> 00:15:07,364
[gentle music playing]

317
00:15:07,448 --> 00:15:09,241
Why is it like that, Miss Cita?

318
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:12,995
I'm so good at finding things
for other people.

319
00:15:13,078 --> 00:15:15,331
So good at finding people.

320
00:15:15,414 --> 00:15:17,374
But for myself,

321
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,293
it feels elusive.

322
00:15:21,295 --> 00:15:22,922
Atoy…

323
00:15:23,505 --> 00:15:25,132
You're only human.

324
00:15:25,215 --> 00:15:27,009
You're not a computer.

325
00:15:28,886 --> 00:15:32,890
Why don't you focus on…

326
00:15:33,557 --> 00:15:37,561
other things, other people, or…

327
00:15:37,645 --> 00:15:39,063
another woman?

328
00:15:40,189 --> 00:15:41,690
Woman? [smirks]

329
00:15:41,774 --> 00:15:43,233
No, Miss Cita.

330
00:15:43,317 --> 00:15:45,611
That's just an additional expense,
and women are headaches.

331
00:15:45,694 --> 00:15:46,654
I'm done with that.

332
00:15:46,737 --> 00:15:49,198
Wait. I didn't mean a girlfriend!

333
00:15:49,281 --> 00:15:50,866
- [in English] Clue!
- [in English] Clue?

334
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:52,660
Mmm. She's persistent!

335
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:54,787
A persistent woman?

336
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:56,580
Always fighting with you!

337
00:15:56,664 --> 00:15:58,499
A woman who always fights with me?

338
00:15:58,582 --> 00:15:59,875
But cute!

339
00:16:01,168 --> 00:16:02,586
- [in English] Cute.
- Mmm.

340
00:16:02,670 --> 00:16:04,004
And persistent?

341
00:16:04,088 --> 00:16:06,632
Good morning, tailors!

342
00:16:06,715 --> 00:16:08,175
Let's get to work!

343
00:16:08,258 --> 00:16:10,386
[whimsical music playing]

344
00:16:10,469 --> 00:16:11,762
Hey!

345
00:16:11,845 --> 00:16:15,057
Psst, hey. What's that--
What are you swiping there?

346
00:16:15,766 --> 00:16:17,267
It's just 40 pesos.

347
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:19,895
I'll buy bread.

348
00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:21,897
If I were stealing,

349
00:16:21,981 --> 00:16:25,359
I'd take the whole thing.

350
00:16:26,026 --> 00:16:27,987
[chuckles]

351
00:16:28,070 --> 00:16:29,947
- I'll buy bread now, okay.
- [Atoy chuckles]

352
00:16:30,030 --> 00:16:31,198
All right, oh--

353
00:16:31,281 --> 00:16:33,450
Oh, be careful!

354
00:16:33,534 --> 00:16:35,035
Yes.

355
00:16:38,872 --> 00:16:40,040
[music concludes]

356
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:42,292
[in English] No, Doc.

357
00:16:43,043 --> 00:16:47,631
[in English] This is a scar
from my appendectomy.

358
00:16:48,132 --> 00:16:51,677
Ma'am, our appendix
is in the lower right abdomen.

359
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:53,053
This one….

360
00:16:53,137 --> 00:16:54,555
Where you feel the pain.

361
00:16:54,638 --> 00:16:55,848
Is this correct?

362
00:16:55,931 --> 00:16:58,475
[tense music playing]

363
00:17:00,144 --> 00:17:02,479
A C-section is here,

364
00:17:03,063 --> 00:17:04,440
below the belly button

365
00:17:05,024 --> 00:17:07,067
and above the pubic bone.

366
00:17:07,651 --> 00:17:11,155
It can be vertical or horizontal cut.

367
00:17:11,655 --> 00:17:13,198
Like yours.

368
00:17:15,534 --> 00:17:19,830
Ma'am, it is impossible for you
to have had an appendectomy before,

369
00:17:19,913 --> 00:17:22,750
because based on your abdominal scan,

370
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:24,418
your appendix is still there.

371
00:17:25,002 --> 00:17:29,298
And the appendix does not
grow back after surgical removal.

372
00:17:29,923 --> 00:17:32,342
[in English] Wait. Where…
Where's the CT scan?

373
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:34,386
[in English] I-I want to see it, Doc.

374
00:17:35,012 --> 00:17:36,096
[in English] Where is it?

375
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:39,475
[in English] Nurse, can I have
the abdominal scan of Ms. Regalia?

376
00:17:39,558 --> 00:17:42,144
[tense music playing]

377
00:17:42,811 --> 00:17:44,563
[doctor, in English] Ma'am,
this is your appendix.

378
00:17:45,814 --> 00:17:47,566
It's still there, but…

379
00:17:47,649 --> 00:17:48,942
um, it's inflamed.

380
00:17:49,026 --> 00:17:51,445
So, we need to operate on you.

381
00:17:52,905 --> 00:17:58,702
[music intensifies]

382
00:18:28,065 --> 00:18:31,026
[in English] You know, it's really nice
that the only thorn in the family

383
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:32,861
decided to take itself out.

384
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:34,071
[pensive music playing]

385
00:18:34,154 --> 00:18:35,280
[sighs]

386
00:18:35,364 --> 00:18:36,824
I can finally breathe…

387
00:18:37,616 --> 00:18:40,619
now that your sister
decided to return to America.

388
00:18:41,787 --> 00:18:43,622
Her decision was sudden.

389
00:18:43,705 --> 00:18:44,748
[suspicious music playing]

390
00:18:44,832 --> 00:18:46,375
Could it be that they already met?

391
00:18:47,084 --> 00:18:48,794
Don't pry anymore.

392
00:18:48,877 --> 00:18:51,421
It's better for us, especially Dad,

393
00:18:51,505 --> 00:18:54,007
that Audrey is not in the Philippines.

394
00:18:54,091 --> 00:18:55,592
We no longer have to worry about

395
00:18:55,676 --> 00:18:59,555
that one thing we've been
hiding from her, right?

396
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:04,017
[music fades]

397
00:19:07,104 --> 00:19:08,105
[ominous music playing]

398
00:19:08,188 --> 00:19:09,398
Hey!

399
00:19:09,481 --> 00:19:10,816
[in English] Careful.

400
00:19:11,483 --> 00:19:12,526
- [in English] Are you okay?
- [in English] Yeah.

401
00:19:16,405 --> 00:19:18,740
[music fades]

402
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:25,247
[indistinct chattering]

403
00:19:25,330 --> 00:19:26,165
Wow.

404
00:19:26,248 --> 00:19:28,333
That's beautiful!

405
00:19:28,417 --> 00:19:30,586
What's that? Uh, a glass?

406
00:19:32,254 --> 00:19:34,256
It's a water tumbler.

407
00:19:34,923 --> 00:19:36,675
Where's your school?

408
00:19:36,758 --> 00:19:37,968
[whimsical music playing]

409
00:19:38,051 --> 00:19:39,928
- Ah…
- Don't you have classes?

410
00:19:40,512 --> 00:19:41,847
Um…

411
00:19:41,930 --> 00:19:43,265
It's nearby.

412
00:19:43,348 --> 00:19:44,766
I'm in the afternoon session,

413
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:46,685
so classes are later.

414
00:19:46,768 --> 00:19:49,104
[sighs] I'm already late.

415
00:19:49,188 --> 00:19:52,357
I won't make it to the flag ceremony.

416
00:19:52,441 --> 00:19:54,026
[in English] Flag ceremony?

417
00:19:54,610 --> 00:19:55,694
What's that?

418
00:19:55,777 --> 00:19:57,738
[in English] Flag ceremony.

419
00:19:57,821 --> 00:19:59,281
You don't know that?

420
00:20:00,199 --> 00:20:02,534
Oh! I know that, I know that.

421
00:20:02,618 --> 00:20:04,828
Um, I was just testing you!

422
00:20:04,912 --> 00:20:07,748
It's just that, a flag ceremony.

423
00:20:07,831 --> 00:20:08,957
What is it again?

424
00:20:21,553 --> 00:20:27,309
[mumbling]

425
00:20:33,148 --> 00:20:34,441
There!

426
00:20:34,524 --> 00:20:36,401
You thought I didn't know.

427
00:20:36,485 --> 00:20:38,278
Teacher said,

428
00:20:38,362 --> 00:20:41,156
"Don't talk when your mouth is full."

429
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:42,908
[gentle music playing]

430
00:20:42,991 --> 00:20:45,911
[man] Child, it's okay now. Let's go.

431
00:20:45,994 --> 00:20:46,995
Time for school.

432
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:51,083
[melancholic music playing]

433
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:53,335
[man] Wait.

434
00:20:56,004 --> 00:20:59,883
Auntie, who told you
that you had surgery before?

435
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:01,885
A doctor in the US?

436
00:21:04,763 --> 00:21:05,847
[in English] No.

437
00:21:08,225 --> 00:21:10,352
- Audrey, darling, Gavin called me.
- [Gavin] Grandpa.

438
00:21:10,936 --> 00:21:12,229
[in English] What happened? Are you okay?

439
00:21:12,312 --> 00:21:14,231
Grandpa, they said she needs surgery.

440
00:21:14,314 --> 00:21:15,732
- [in English] Dad…
- [in English] What?

441
00:21:16,441 --> 00:21:17,651
[in English] Dad.

442
00:21:18,485 --> 00:21:23,782
[in English] you told me that I had
an appendectomy while I was in a coma.

443
00:21:24,574 --> 00:21:28,453
But here in my CT scan,
my appendix is still here.

444
00:21:28,537 --> 00:21:29,413
There, look!

445
00:21:29,496 --> 00:21:31,081
- [dramatic sting]
- [sinister music playing]

446
00:21:31,915 --> 00:21:34,960
[in English] Why did you lie to me
about having an appendectomy?

447
00:21:36,378 --> 00:21:37,879
[in English] You know what else?

448
00:21:38,964 --> 00:21:40,507
The doctor here said…

449
00:21:42,259 --> 00:21:43,635
that this scar…

450
00:21:45,512 --> 00:21:48,598
This scar is from a cesarean section

451
00:21:48,682 --> 00:21:50,892
and not from an appendectomy.

452
00:21:50,976 --> 00:21:52,644
[music intensifies]

453
00:21:53,645 --> 00:21:55,439
[Audrey] So, what's the truth, Dad?

454
00:21:56,690 --> 00:21:58,275
Was I pregnant then?

455
00:21:59,568 --> 00:22:01,570
Which doctor told you that?

456
00:22:01,653 --> 00:22:03,655
[Audrey] Just yes or no, Dad!

457
00:22:03,739 --> 00:22:05,532
Why can't you answer me?

458
00:22:05,615 --> 00:22:10,120
[in English] Was I pregnant
while I was in a coma?!

459
00:22:10,203 --> 00:22:12,039
[in English] Let's just talk about this
after your surgery.

460
00:22:12,122 --> 00:22:14,041
[Audrey] Just yes or no, Dad!

461
00:22:14,624 --> 00:22:16,168
Why can't you answer me?

462
00:22:16,668 --> 00:22:19,963
[in English] So, you can think
of an excuse and lie to my face?!

463
00:22:21,423 --> 00:22:23,008
Say something!

464
00:22:23,842 --> 00:22:24,676
‪[pained breathing]

465
00:22:27,179 --> 00:22:28,180
[in English] Yes.

466
00:22:28,263 --> 00:22:29,389
[music fades]

467
00:22:29,473 --> 00:22:30,766
You were pregnant then.

468
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:35,687
[intense music playing]

469
00:22:47,157 --> 00:22:48,742
[music fades]

470
00:22:48,825 --> 00:22:53,121
[electronic blipping]

471
00:22:58,376 --> 00:23:00,045
Oh, frog! Hey!

472
00:23:00,128 --> 00:23:02,214
Got you. You didn't apologize to me.

473
00:23:02,297 --> 00:23:03,215
UP NEXT

474
00:23:03,298 --> 00:23:05,425
- You really are something!
- [woman, in English] That's my car!

475
00:23:06,218 --> 00:23:08,011
I won't charge you, since…

476
00:23:08,095 --> 00:23:10,347
I don't think you guys
can afford to pay it anyway.

477
00:23:10,430 --> 00:23:11,306
How much is it?

478
00:23:11,389 --> 00:23:12,390
Whoa!

479
00:23:12,891 --> 00:23:14,392
[in English] I don't like your tone.

480
00:23:14,476 --> 00:23:16,228
What's happening to you?
Why don't you want to study?

481
00:23:16,311 --> 00:23:17,395
This is for your own good.

482
00:23:17,479 --> 00:23:20,148
I don't know how to read or write.

483
00:23:20,232 --> 00:23:23,110
Isn't she looking for her real parents?

484
00:23:23,193 --> 00:23:25,946
Ibyang grew up in the orphanage.

485
00:23:26,029 --> 00:23:29,116
How could she look for something

486
00:23:29,199 --> 00:23:30,700
she doesn't know and doesn't understand?

487
00:23:30,784 --> 00:23:33,829
You really were the one
who brought my child to the orphanage?

488
00:23:33,912 --> 00:23:35,330
[in English] It was a huge mistake.

489
00:23:35,413 --> 00:23:36,748
We're already looking for the child.

490
00:23:36,832 --> 00:23:38,041
[Cita] <i>What's that for?</i>

491
00:23:38,125 --> 00:23:39,918
I have to go to a convent,

492
00:23:40,001 --> 00:23:42,129
to talk to Sister Norma.

493
00:23:42,212 --> 00:23:45,465
<i>She's the only one who knows</i>
<i>where Ibyang really came from.</i>

494
00:23:45,549 --> 00:23:47,092
[woman, in Engish] <i>Good morning, Sister.</i>

495
00:23:47,175 --> 00:23:48,677
Grandchild, bless.

496
00:23:49,761 --> 00:23:51,429
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

497
00:23:51,513 --> 00:23:53,515
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

498
00:23:53,598 --> 00:23:55,433
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪
